text: Eva Leanza Cornett (June 10, 1971 - October 28, 2020) was an American television personality and beauty pageant title holder. She was Miss Florida 1992 and later Miss America 1993. She was also a stage actress. As Miss America, Cornett was the first beauty queen to adopt AIDS prevention as the theme of her service year. She was earlier National Sweetheart 1991. Cornett was married to Mark Steines from 1995 to 2013. After 17 years, they got divorced. Cornett was born in Big Stone Gap, Virginia. She was later raised in Jacksonville, Florida. Cornett died on October 28, 2020 from a subdural hematoma caused by a fall at a Jacksonville hospital, aged 49. ==References== Category:Actors from Jacksonville, Florida Category:Miss America winners Category:1971 births Category:2020 deaths Category:Deaths from subdural hematoma Category:Accidental deaths from falls in the United States Category:American stage actors Category:Actors from Virginia Category:American models
